reviewText: 80-76%-perfect75-71%-awsome70-66%-good65-61%-poor60-56%-awful1. Rick Flair vs. Carltio for the ITC title- this was a good choice as an opener. I think because usually whenever flair is in a match he gets the crowd involved. This one is no different. I thought there were some slow spots in the match but I really did not know who was going to win the match. A good part is when flair comes off the top rope for the first time. Decent opener. Match Rating 7/10.2. Trish and Ashley vs. Victoria and torrie wilison- this was alot better than i expected. I did not think ashley was ready to get in the ring yet but she did a preatty good job. Your decent womens tag with nothing special but i did enjoy when trish got the tag the pace picked up and the crowd was into the match. Decent match. Winners trish and ashley. Match Rating 5.5/10.3. Big Show vs. Gene Snitsky- I was not expecting alot from this match and we did not get alot either. It was just about a 7 minute match with big men action. The best part was when snitsky backsuplexed the big show that was neat. Big show carried the match and this was nothing special. Winner the big show. Match Rating 5/10.4. Kerwin White vs. Shelton Benjamin- I thought this was a good match. I dont think it was as enjoyable because of chavo new role. It was still watchable as i think both men have alot of talent and are under used. Decent match. Winner Shelton Benjamin. Match Rating 6.5/10.5. Edge vs. matt hardy in a steel cage match- This was an awsome match. Match of the night and match of the year in my opinion a match of the year possibility. These guys broght all they had to the table. So many things were right about this match. First off the storyline was great. This was a real life stituation and it played into a perfect storyline. When you watch the first 11 minutes it is just okay but the last 8 minutes were awsome. Blood and everything. Best Part hardy hits his leg drop off a 15 foot high steel cage. Have to see to believe. Winner matt hardy. Match Rating 10/10.6. Trevor Merdoch and lance cade vs. The hurrican and rosey- What ever happened to tag team wrestling. I think the wwe as forgot how important this division is. This was an okay match but i was glad to see the titles switch hands. I wanted to see what cade and murdoch could do with the titles. A sick ddt on the floor. Winners and new wwe tag team champs cade and murdoch. Match Rating 5/10.7. Shawn Michales vs. Chris Masters- This was a good match. I would say this was the best so far that masters had ever been in. I think it also helped that michales was the other guy as he carried most of the match. There were some nice shots with masters slaming michales bask into the ring post. One problem was that michales back was worked on alot in this match. THere was alot of action in the last 6 minutes which brings my rating up. Winner shawn michales. Match rating 8.5/10.8. Kurt Angle vs. John cena for the wwe title- THis match was going awsome untill cena got dq. I was looking so much foward to this match sience they had put on an awsome match at no way out but the dq brought it down big and sience it was the mania event that hurt it to. Before that everthing was great some good back and forth action. Some good after math as well. Winner kurt angle by dq. Match Rating 7/10.Well that raps up another. The rating that i would give unforgiven 2005 is a 55/80 which is a 86% which means it is a good ppv. I think that is a good rating. I would get this for under 20 dollars and the hardy edge match was awsome. I would appericate it if you would tell me if my review was helpful or not. You can check out my other reviews by clicking on other reviews. Tanks for your time.

reviewText: I ordered this WWE event on PPV and watched it live, and it turned out to be a pretty good show. I wasn't expecting to see Ric Flair take the WWE IC title from Carlito. I thought Carlito would probably cheat like he always does and leave with the belt, but Flair's victory was a huge surprise! Flair was also very funny during and after this match. Edge & Matt Hardy battled in a brutal, thrilling steel cage match. It had some sick bumps, but the most spectacular one was when Matt delivered a leg drop from the top of the cage! Wow! What a match! Lita even got a taste of her own medicine via the "twist of fate" from Matt Hardy. The only real drawback of this PPV is the bull**** DQ during the main event match between John Cena & Kurt Angle. That is absolutely uncalled for! When something like that happens on WWE Raw or Smackdown, I can tolerate it. But for heaven's sake, I paid 30 dollars for this PPV and I don't deserve a stupid DQ in the main event match up! Oh, well, this was still a good show.

reviewText: I say its a rare case because the extra match on the dvd is probably the best match on the dvd. It was the main event from Raw the night after this PPV and featured a excellent 4 on 4 match with Big Show, Matt Hardy, Shawn Michaels, and John Cena VS Edge, Kurt Angle, Snitsky, and Chris Masters. Not saying this PPV sucked though, it was pretty good.Ric Flair VS Carlito: After losing most of his matches for the past few years, WWE finally decides to let Flair hold some gold. Its his first IC title and says its his greatest achievement. Yea right. This was a good way to start the PPV.Trish and Ashley VS Torrie and Victora: If you read all my WWE reviews you'll know im not down with women wrestling.Big Show VS Snitsky: You wouldnt expect a different match between this two wrestlers. I thought it went well though for what it was.Shelton Benjamin VS Kerwin White: Kerwin White. Its one of the worst ideas of all time and im glad they got rid of this guy. The match was good but nothing really speical.Edge VS Matt Hardy: A very good steel cage match. Its nice to see WWE finally give Hardy a win instead of Edge all the time.Rosey and Hurricane VS Cade and Murdoch: Bathroom break. The titles change hands but who really cares? The tag team divsion is very weak on Raw that im surprised they didnt get rid of the titles all together.I love Maria. She is so cute and I find some of her interviews to be quite funny. The one she does with Masters before the match is one of the funniest interviews ive seen in a very long time from WWE. A must watch.Shawn Michaels VS Chris Masters: A very good match. I thought the ending was well done. Id agree its Masters best match, considering I havent seen too much of this guy.Kurt Angle VS John Cena: Is this the reason why Angle left WWE? Sure he went to Smackdown and won the title but I guess that wasnt good enough for him. Come to think of it, it seems all losers to Cena went to Smackdown and won the title. Coincidence or not, the match was good up until the end.Overall, a pretty good PPV by Raw. Like I said, the extra match from Raw the next night was probably the best match on the whole dvd.

reviewText: 1. Intercontinental Title Match: Carlito (c) vs. Ric FlairGood way to start the show, these two big personalities collide in a very entertaining match. Flair proves that he can still have good matches and win titles at his age, and the crowd really gets behind him. Also, Flair finally hits a move off the tope rope! The crowd goes nuts for that. Overall a good opener, gets the crowd very excited for the show. 7/102. Trish Stratus & Ashley Massaro vs. Torrie Wilson & VictoriaStandard women's tag match, skip this, it isn't worth your time. 4/103. Big Show vs. SnitskyGoing into this, I thought this would be painfully boring. It isn't as slow as I imagined, but it is quite obvious that Big Show carries the entire match. Snitsky is an absolutely horrendous wrestler, but Big Show does a pretty good job making up for it, and he actually makes this one relatively entertaining. Worth a watch, but I wouldn't go back to this one. 5.5/104. Shelton Benjamin vs. Kerwin WhiteKerwin White is Chavo Guerrero's attempt at a "typical middle class white man" gimmick. While hilariously awful, it limits Chavo somewhat and doesn't allow him to have the good match that him and Shelton should have had. This match isn't bad, but not much happens here, and Shelton picks up the easy win. Take a look at this one once, if just to see Chavo drive a golf cart to the ring, wearing a sweater with bleached blonde hair. 5/105. Steel Cage Match: Matt Hardy vs. EdgeFinally, these two get the time and the stipulation that allows them to truly shine. This match is a classic Steel Cage match, and after a poor confrontation at Summerslam, this is quite welcome. This fued was dying for a brutal stipulation, and thats what the Steel Cage provided. Not only does this match have great, breathtaking spots, but its also very well wrestled. Matt Hardy and Edge both prove here that they are deserving of the 20 or so minutes that they are given, and they truly make the best of them. The crowd is on their feet nearly the entire time, cheering on these two for wonderful performances, and rightfully so. This is just an excellent match, with a fantastic ending that I won't spoil. 9.25/106. World Tag Team Championship Match: The Hurricane & Rosey (c) vs. Lance Cade & Trevor MurdochThis is rather boring, as neither team is anything special in the ring. The match is uneventful to say the least, and isn't worth your time, other then the one spot where Trevor Murdoch DDT's Hurricane off of the ring apron straight onto the ringside floor. I spoiled that spot for you, simply because you shouldn't have to watch the rest of the match waiting for it. Overall, this is lame and unexciting, skip if you've already seen the viscious DDT. 4/107. Shawn Michaels vs. Chris MastersI was fairly suprised by this, but then I remembered that HBK was in this one for a reason. The Showstopper and the Masterpiece have a good, back and forth match here. Shawn makes Masters look pretty good, and puts on yet another great performance himself. They gave this one just the right amount of time, and this match has an excellent pace. Great ending to a good match, don't pass this up. 7.5/108. WWE Championship Match: John Cena (c) vs. Kurt AngleAngle and Cena have had many matches, but this just may be their best. These two bring a great amount of intensity to the table in this one, and make the whole atmosphere very exciting. They really work well together, and put on a great title bout. Other then the ending, this match is probably one of Cena's best matches in the WWE to date. Both men put on great performances on this one, and make this one a great match other then the DQ ending. Of course, the ref ringing the bell doesn't stop these two from fighting, because they continue until one of them ends up through an announce table (I won't spoil it for you, watch what happens). Overall, a very good match with a slightly annoying finish. 8.5/10Unforgiven 2005 is yet another great single brand PPV from 2005, as most matches deliver. Some are lackluster, but the uppercard is solid. There are four good matches that make this worth your time.Match of the Night: The Steel Cage match: Matt Hardy vs. Edge. These two have a very brutal and very entertaining match, with excellent pacing and wonderful spots, as well as good wrestling. This is everything you could have asked for from these two, and they put on a great show. Don't miss this, this is one of the better matches of the year.

reviewText: An ok WWE pay-per view! The WWE Championship wasn't what I expected, but of course John Cena retaining the freakin' title was expected! Just not the greatest WWE Championship match... (3/5) Intercontinental Championship match between Ric Flair and Carlito was pointless?! (2/5) The Steel Cage Match between Matt Hardy and Edge w/ Lita was one of the greatest grudge matches of all-time! (5/5) Shawn Michaels vs. Chris Masters again pointless! The World Tag Team Championship match was pretty great, unlike the tag-teams of now... both these tag-teams had chemistry and likeliness and weren't just pushed together for the sake of it! (4/5) Big Show vs. Snitsky I expected to be downright stupid but actually wasn't half bad! (4/5) Trish + Ashley vs. Victoria + Torrie w/ Candice was one of the best Women's tag-team matches seen in a long while up to this point. (4/5) And Finally Shelton Benjamin vs. Kerwin White = stupid set-up and just downright horrible! The Kerwin character wasn't smart to do anyway! (1/5) So over-all (3/5) pay-per view! So pretty much average... certainly not their greatest!!!

reviewText: I'll be fair this time. WWE honestly seems like they're either running out of ideas, or running out of talent, which would be their own fault by the way. It's like they're not even trying to please a wrestling audience. Now some of the "Entertainment" is pretty funny at times, but you start to notice that's almost the entire show, and very little wrestling. And plus everything is very predictable. At the rate WWE is going, a "Main Eventer" can really only have about a 6 to 8 year run. Why? They don't follow wrestling tradition...meaning, they don't expose their "bottom guys" and give them a chance(by the script). They just put em' heat or velocity, which like no one watches. And that's one of the reasons why the titles have absoluty no value anymore. And oh yes they do need a new champ?,But who are they gonna give the title to? This where only showcasing the "big names" comes back to bite WWE in the butt. And you can't keep asking guys like HBK to be the champ and head the company, or bring value back to the title. Those guys are simply there to put the young guys over. But no one will believe it when it happens because there's way too much comedy and hollywood production going on. And for that,WWE fans will never be as loyal as ECW or TNA fans in the end.Now as for TNA, will they really ever put WWE out of buisness? NO! There just like ECW; They're not really meant to be in Madison Square Garden, which is not a bad thing at all. And as far as I'm concerned, Christopher Daniels, A.J. Styles, and Petey Williams are a lot better than most of what WWE is putting out there. Also a few of their paper-views were way better that WWE's. However, TNA's regular shows are pretty much crap. All in all, I've been a wrestling fan for 16 years now, and I'm just trying not to loose faith.

reviewText: When collecting WWE PPV's from this particular year, this one along with WWE Vengeance 2005, ECW One Night Stand 2005, WWE Judgment Day 2005 WWE Taboo Tuesday and WWE Survivor Series 2005 are MUST HAVE'S!Now, let's get to the card:Carlito Vs. Ric Flair (WWE I-C title match) - While in his late 50's, I have to give credit to Flair. He can still put on a good match. Carlito was just getting into his character by this point as well as being I-C champ. Match ends with Ric punching Carlito as he was preparing to spit his apple into Flair's face, causing him to choke! As he was trying to get his breath, Flair slaps on the Figure Four leglock for a quick submission and his first I-C title!Ashley & Trish Stratus Vs. Victoria & Torrie Wilson w/Candice Michelle - Nice to look at but not much here. Worth a look but not a repeated look. Ends when Trish connects on Victoria with her "chick kick."The Big Show Vs. Snitsky - Decent match for two big men. Ends with TBS' patened chokeslam for the win and followed up by a vicious assault with the ringbell on Snitsky after the match!Edge w/Lita Vs. Matt Hardy (Steel Cage Bout) - Let me say this, this has to be one of the best cage matches of all time! I don't care if you are talking about Hell In The Cell, Thundercage, WarGames or any other version of this type of match, this one ranks right up there and the real life situation only made it even sweeter! Jake Roberts was right on his DVD when he said you don't always need a title belt to make a good match, you need a situation that people can understand and can sympathize with. I mean, there isn't a man out there that HASN'T had what happened to Matt Hardy happen to them OR knew someone that it has happened to (I think you all know the situation so no need for me to go into it)!Anyway, the match itself was a classic and the ending was a la "Superfly" Jimmy Snuka from the 80's or Rikishi's dive off the top of the cage on Val Venus back earlier in this decade! DEFINTELY MATCH OF THE NIGHT BOTH IN PERFORMANCE AND DRAMA!Shawn Michaels Vs. Chris Masters - This match proved once again why "HBK" is one of the best in the business as he made Masters look like a "million bucks." Masters pretty much dominates this match but can't get his "Masterlock" on Michaels. The one time he does lock it on, Michaels is able to get to the ropes for an escape. Match ends when in another attempt to put on the "ML", Michaels slips out and gives Masters "Sweet Chin Music" and you know what happens after that! Great match!Huricane & Rosey Vs. Cade & Murdoch (WWE World Tag Team Title Match) - Nothing special. Just your standard tag team title match. Belts did change hands though.Kurt Angle Vs. John Cena (WWE Title Match) - Pretty good encounter. Didn't care for the ending but it is still worth a look. Angle is the superior performer without a doubt but I'll give Cena credit. He is, as I have pointed out in other reviews, competent enough to take direction from superior talent like Angle to put on a great show.BONUS MATCH:John Cena, Matt Hardy, The Big Show & Shawn Michaels Vs. Chris Masters, Edge, Snitsky & Kurt Angle - VERY WILD 8-MAN TAG FROM THE NEXT NIGHT ON RAW!Overall, this one is worth a buy!

reviewText: I love this ppv so much. It had great matches.IC Champ Carlito vs. Ric Flair- Good opener, it's good to see Flair as a Babyface again. Plus it's really great to see Flair become the IC champ. This match shouldn't have been an opener, it should have happened later that night. But still a good match. Winner and new IC Champ- Ric FlairDivas Tag Match: Trish & Ashley vs. Torrie & Victoria- Pretty good for a divas match. Wow Ashley sure can wrestle. - Winners Trish and Ashley.Big Show vs. Snitsky- This was a funny match. I liked it when Snitsky suplexes the Big Show. Show gets his revenge by hitting Snitsky with the ring Bell. Winner- Big ShowShelton Benjamin vs. Kerwin White- This match turned up better then I thought. That whole K-white gimmick was pretty bad for Chovo.- Winner- Shelton BenjaminSteel Cage- Matt Hardy vs. Edge- BEST MATCH OF THE NIGHT. This had a great story between Hardy, Edge and Lita. Edge bleed like hell. The best part is when Hardy did the leg drop off the cage. This story should have went on longer. This was the one of the best bouts on RAW next to HHH and HBK. Winner- Matt HardyTag Champs- The Super Heros vs. The Cowboys- This was a boring match to me. It was more of a handicap with Rosey getting his ass kicked. Winners and New Champs- The CowboysShawn Micheals vs. Chris Masters- This was the 2nd best match. Finally, Masters wrestles some real wrestlers. It was funny to see how Shawn Micheals survived the Master lock. Winner- Shawn MichealsWWE Champ John Cena vs. Kurt Angle- I don't know why everyone hates Cena. Every time someone becomes WWE champ, everyone hates that champ. Like everyone wanted to see JBL lose the title and he did to Cena, now everyone hates Cena. Now the match was great. It would have been better if Cena didn't get DQ. It was great to see him give an FU to Angle and Bishoff. Winner by DQ- Kurt Angle (Cena retains)This PPV was the "PPV OF THE YEAR".
summary: THIS IS THE PPV OF THE YEAR!

reviewText: Intercontinental ChampionshipCarlito vs Ric Flair 8/10- a much better match than i anticipated. Flair at 55 is twice the man that Carlito is. Ric shows he can still perform against someone 30 yrs younger than him. a must see ending in this is what makes this match special.disgusting segment with Edge & Lita in the locker room.Torrie Wilson & Victoria(w/ Candace Michelle) vs Trish Stratus & Ashley 7.5/10- expected a dud as it usually is with women's matches. the best women's match in almost a year. Status return is a welcomed sign . Ashley has potential, but is still green. all women should fight in tag team matches. it makes it more interesting.fantastic backstage segment with Ric Flair & some young ladies.Snitsky vs Big Show 7.5/10- this one was actually interesting. these 2 go at it with some intense moments.funny moments with Ric Flair in his limo.Kerwin White vs Shelton Benjamin 7/10- this actually is the worst match on the card with a 7 rating. White should go back to being Chavo. his gimmick is so lame. some good moments, but could have been much more with these 2.curious interview with Matt Hardy.Steel Cage MatchEdge vs Matt Hardy 10/10- a match of the year candidate. much better than Summerslam! this 2 turn the clock back 5 yrs to their glory days in tag wrestling. all out intensity including Lita trying to interfere a few times. these 2's hatred for one another just adds to this semi shoot match.a must watch segment in the trainer's room involving Eric Bischoff & John Cena.World Tag Team ChampionshipHurricane & Rosey vs Lance Cade & Trevor Murdoch 8/10- a throwback to old school tag team wrestling. the superheros surprisingly long title reign is put to the test here.  Cade & Murdoch are impressive as a tag team. Trevor is the son of Captain Redneck Dick Murdoch. he is the spitting image of dad & is a chip off the old block.more backstage antics with Ric Flair.Maria, the dingbat, interviews Chris Masters.Chris Masters vs Shawn Michaels 9.5/10- an excellent match for Masters 1st big test. Masters @ 22 & Michaels @ 41 makes Shawn old enough to be his dad. hard to believe that! Masterpiece is very impressive for a muscle guy. reminds me of Lex Luger except Chris can actually wrestle. this one will keep your attention.Flair's grand exit backstage.WWE ChampionshipJohn Cena vs Kurt Angle 9/10- these 2 always put on a good show together. Kurt brings out the best in John. Cena seems to do his best work with Angle. very good matchup . the lame ending is the only dark spot on the match.Extras include a 8 man tag match from the next night on Raw. this is Raw's best ppv of the year. good luck to Smackdown on trying to duplicate this one.

reviewText: 1.  Very good and funny match. Flair can still wrestle very well. He still has all the tricks up his sleeve. Flair wins to become the new interconinental champion! 8.5/102. Trish and Ashley vs Torrie Wilson and Victoria- This was the best women's match I have seen in quite some time. Trish was ready for this match and her return match was great. 7/103. Big Show vs Snitsky- This match was alright. Big Show will get his push soon in my opinion. The aftermath of this match was good. 5/104. Shelton Benjamin vs Kerwin White- I am glad shelton won this match. He deserves a wwe title match. He has beaten a lot of great people including jericho and triple h. The match was pretty good. 6.5/105. Matt Hardy vs Edge- This match was unbelieveable. I was thinking in the first 20 or so minutes where was the blood? Then edge bleeds. This match was absolutely crazy. Lita interfeared and got the twist of fate. The ending was absolutely fantastic when Matt did a legdrop from the top of the cage!!!! 10/10 Match of the Year!!!!!!!6. reviewText: Pretty much every match(except for one)was nothing less than good.Two of the matches were exceptionally good.1.Ric Flair vs. Carlito(WWE Intercontinental Championship)This was a good match.It was slow at spots,but it was made up for by two things:1-Flair's happiness after the match(You'll see what I mean)and 2-Flair FINALLY HIT A MOVE OFF THE TOP ROPE!He was very happy about this.7 out of 10.2.Trish Stratus and Ashley vs. Torrie Wilson and VictoriaNothing special here.This was the exception I was talking about before.Everythings been used before.5 out of 10.3.Big Show vs. SnitskyThis was a good big man matchup.I like Snitsky and I think he should get a push like he did when he fueded with Kane.Good match overall,but again nothing overly great.7 out of 10.4.Kerwin White vs. Shelton BenjaminI'm glad that Chavo got rid of this gimmick.I'm also unhappy that Shelton's got the "momma" gimmick because it makes him look stupid.But anyway,this match was like the opener,except a little quicker paced.I liked the way that Shelton did the T-Bone at the end.7 out of 10.5.Steel Cage MatchMatt Hardy vs. EdgeThis was the way a cage match should be done.Now granted, the match did get a little slow in the middle,the last 6 or 7 minutes were crazy.This match proved why these two should be in the main events.(Edge did go there quicker than Matt did though)The match was capped off with an insane leg drop off the top rope.10 out of 10.6.The Hurricane and Rosey vs. Trevor Murdoch and Lance Cade(World Tag Team Championship)This was a good tag team match; better than what I expected.The Hurricane took a sick DDT off the apron to the outside.7 out of 10.7.Shawn Michaels vs. Chris MastersThis was a good matchup.Great start and great end to the match.The middle was a little slow,but the quick paced beginning and the quick paced ending more than makeup for it.8 out of 10.8.John Cena vs. Kurt Angle(WWE Championship)Out of all the matches I've seen including these two,(about 4)I would not give one of them under an 8.(Even Cena's debut against Angle)This is no different.Even though it did have a DQ ending,the whole match itself was just great and what happened after the match was good too.9 out of 10.I recommend this to anyone.

reviewText: I took a glance at my WWE DVD collection (got about 100 or more), and I stared at the 2005 PPV section I have.  I remembered that I used to watch RAW every single night in 2005.  SmackDown was pretty strange that year, but RAW was just exciting TV week in and week out.  I grabbed "Unforgiven 2005" to take a trip down memory lane.  Not only is it just as good as I remembered it, it's may be even better this time around.Don't worry...a match-by-match breakdown is coming up.  I just have to proclaim that while many pro wrestling fans miss the Attitude Era (1997-2001, approx.), I miss the must-see TV that RAW was in 2005.  Seriously, let's recap this:* Evolution finally crumbles with the Batista/HHH rivalry* Randy Orton challenges Undertaker to "WrestleMania" (both shows got this program)* The Shawn Michaels and Kurt Angle rivalry (mostly a RAW feud)* John Cena comes to RAW* John Cena starts to get booed...a lot* Hulk Hogan and HBK: Icon vs. Legend* The Edge/Lita/Matt Hardy triangle* Chris Jericho and Eric Bischoff get "fired" (sad moments, but VERY well-done)* Ric Flair gets his groove back* Even younger guys like Shelton Benjamin, Chris Masters, and Carlito appeared to be the real dealSo, where am I going with this train-of-thought?  Simple, 2005 was an excellent year for Monday Night RAW, and "Unforgiven 2005" is a great example of that.1) Intercontinental ChampionshipRic Flair v. Carlito (champion)---"What's a 16-time world champion doing in a match like this?"  I thought the same thing, but when the match got going, I stopped caring.  This opener is all about charisma and psychology.  Sure, the wrestling is pretty basic, with Flair's counter-offense being mostly chops to the chest.  But thanks to a wild Oklahoma City crowd, a hilarious aftermath, and some neat surprises (Hint: Flair on the top rope), I enjoyed this one.  It's one of those matches my mind tears apart, but by smiles and laughs won me over."6.5 / 10"------------------------------------------------2) Torrie Wilson & Victoria (w/ Candice Michelle) v.Trish Stratus (Women's champion) & Ashley Masarro---Admittedly, this one doesn't look like much on paper.  And to be honest, Ashley's rookie performance stands out in a bad way.  But thanks to Trish & Victoria, this tag team match moves pretty well and has some convincing action.  And Candice Michelle at ringside...HOT!  In all seriousness, this isn't one of the best Diva matches around, but it has more hits than misses."6.0 / 10"------------------------------------------------3) Big Show v. Gene Snitsky---I'm one of the few people that thought Gene Snitsky was entertaining because he was so out there and could move pretty well for a larger athlete.  I thought his combination of speed & strength made for a good contest, just like how Brock Lesnar & Big Show gelled together.  Like the Divas tag team match, this grudge match is nothing to go out of your way to see.  But because it's faster-paced than most giant-vs-giant matches, it's entertaining while it lasts.  Besides, it's only about 6 minutes, so it'll be over soon if you're not digging it."6.0 / 10"------------------------------------------------4) Kerwin White v. Shelton Benjamin---Quick history lesson:  Chavo Guerrero changed his persona to a wannabe upper-class guy rode in on a golf cart, died his hair blonde, had Vegas-style music, and dressed like a rich man's casual wardrobe.  Chavo stopped using this character after Eddie Guerrero died a couple months later.  However, I think Kerwin White was a hilarious character, thanks to Chavo's comedic talent.  Thankfully, Kerwin White was still a solid in-ring wrestler, while Shelton Benjamin was at the top of his game in 2005.  These two just had a good back-and-forth wrestling match.  Sometimes that's all I want to see, and the contrasting styles between these two men made for some good action."7.0 / 10"------------------------------------------------5) Steel Cage MatchEdge (w/ Lita) v. Matt Hardy---Okay, so if you're a skeptic, you've noticed that "Unforgiven 2005" so far could be argued as a meaningless endeavor.  But boy, does business ever pick up here!  Quite possibly the most realistically heated rivalry in WWE history, this love triangle made for some good TV going in.  And this Steel Cage Match was just the strong apex the feud deserved.  These two just wail on each other, and genuinely seem like they're trying to kill each other.  It's just a good old fashioned fight with some Steel Cage highspots thrown in for good measure.  I have to admit I had the usual Cage-Logic questions (Why is there a door anyway?  Why climb over the top?  Etc).  But besides those quibbles, I really dug this fight, and most viewers will too.  This one will surely go down as an Edge classic, a Matt Hardy classic, and a Steel Cage classic."8.0 / 10"------------------------------------------------6) World Tag Team ChampionshipsLance Cade & Trevor Murdoch v. The Hurricane & Rosey (champions)---This match doesn't get a lot of good reviews, and I don't understand why.  You have two completely different teams.  You have meaningful twists & action that occurs beyond the in-ring contest.  You have 3 guys who are very gifted athletes, as well as the giant Rosey being more than just a slow slug.  And the final turn-of-events is good old fashioned storytelling psychology.  I wish the match were a little bit longer, but in a weird way, that's one of the best compliments you can give to a match."7.0 / 10"------------------------------------------------7) Chris Masters v. Shawn Michaels---I don't care what the naysayers think; Chris Masters was on a huge roll.  His cocky promos were solid.  He had a great body (steroid-enhanced perhaps).  His Masterlock Challenges were always entertaining.  And his Pass-The-Torch storyline with HBK was a great next step.  In 2005, Masters was delivering quality entertainment.  But it takes two to tango, and who better to get off the ground than with Shawn Michaels?  This match is simply amazing, from start to finish.  Masters gets the early advantage before the bell even rings, yet Michaels fights with everything he has while simultaneously avoiding the Masterlock hold.  Both guys dish it out, and both guys sell well.  As much as I usually dislike HBK's signature comeback, there's some great twists on the usual routine.  And the finish...just freaking wow!  This whole grudge match delivers!  This is by far my favorite match from the PPV, and I think it's one of 2005's finest matches."9.0 / 10"------------------------------------------------8) WWE ChampionshipKurt Angle v. John Cena (champion)---It's a testament to both of these men that this match doesn't feel like a retread of their pivotal "No Mercy 2003" and "No Way Out 2005" encounters.  This PPV main event stands on its own merits, with the aggressive technician Angle clashing with the tough brawler Cena.  The whole match just flows well, regardless if you think one wrestler is "carrying" the other or not.  Both men deserve a ton of credit for keeping the Oklahoma City crowd excited, because this audience was already making a ton of non-stop noise throughout the PPV.  Some might frown at the DQ finish; I personally don't mind them when they're as well-done as this.  Eric Bischoff's involvement is so well-executed that you just love to hate the conniving bastard.  Besides, this match was so good, why ruin the first round with a clean finish?  I know I was ready for Cena/Angle Round 2."7.5 / 10"BONUS MATCHFrom RAW 9/19/20058-Man Tag Team MatchEdge, Gene Snitsky, Chris Masters, & Kurt Angle v.Shawn Michaels, Big Show, Matt Hardy, & John Cena---This was a rematch between 4 of the PPV grudge matches, and it clocks in at about 18 minutes.  It's one of the better TV main events.  I wouldn't give it Match-of-the-Year honors, or anything like that.  But the Texas crowd just ate this one up, and it's nice to see the different styles mix it up, complete with a nice crowd-pleasing finish.  Good stuff, here."7.0 / 10" (very good for a TV match)OVERALL---The key word I pick to describe "Unforgiven 2005" is FUN.  It's just fun to watch this card.  A ton of credit has to go to the Oklahoma City crowd for making even the most mundane moment feel special.  I love the variety of content from the card.  Ric Flair's post-match celebration is one of the funniest things in WWE.  You get a few harmless, fun matches involving Divas, giants, & a Mexican who wants to be a white boy.  And then the intensity picks up for the other 2 hours, thanks to a memorable Steel Cage Match, an underrated Tag Titles Match, one of the best matches from either Chris Masters or Shawn Michaels, and a good solid championship main event with a promise that more is to come."Unforgiven 2005" is a great way to kill 3 hours.  Buy It!
summary: RAW's 2005 Season Shines Once Again On PPV

reviewText: Although there are smaller federations out there with a better product than WWE (TNA, ROH, etc.), Unforgiven 2005 was a good show nonetheless, and is actually one of my favorites (and I own about 40 WWE pay-per-views). It wasn't the best RAW PPV of 2005 (that was Vengeance), but it certainly wasn't the worst, either (New Year's Revolution). I'd say it almost rivals Backlash in terms of quality and entertainment, which is pretty good. So let's get started. (Matches are rated out of 5 stars.)1. IC TITLE: Ric Flair vs. Carlito (c)Never thought I'd be seeing something like this, but it really happened. Not only does Flair put on a great performance for his age and succeed in doing a top-rope move for (maybe) the first time in 22 years, he also wins his first-ever Intercontinental Championship from Carlito and parties all night long. I'll spare you any further details about that...but it was the win that counted.WINNER: Ric Flair. STARS: **1/2.2. Victoria and Torrie Wilson w/Candace vs. Trish Stratus and Ashley MassaroDisastrous women's matches are par for the WWE's course, as we all know...but this one was actually sort of watchable, if only because we got to see Ashley from some, uh, very interesting angles...and Trish pulled off some great moves in there when she finally got tagged in. I'm glad she's back.WINNERS: Trish and Ashley. STARS: *1/2.3. Big Show vs. Gene SnitskyDefinitely the worst match of the event (besides the divas thing), but still okay. Basically an exchange of big-man power moves, but they didn't drag it out too long, and at least it ended right.WINNER: Big Show. STARS: *1/2.4. Kerwin White vs. Shelton BenjaminChavo was burying his career in this gimmick; basically, he dyed his hair blonde and pretended to be a middle-class white guy. But he still put on a pretty good match with Shelton; the spinning headscissors was poetry in motion. Shelton takes it with the T-Bone Suplex. What happened to this guy's push?WINNER: Shelton Benjamin. STARS: **1/2.5. CAGE MATCH: Edge w/Lita vs. Matt HardyA very intense feud going into this one, and it was about time WWE showed Matt some respect. I wouldn't say it was match of the year, like some people claimed, but it was quite a battle and pretty much stole the undercard. After lots of very realistic and painful brawling, Matt gets the win with an incredible legdrop off the top of the cage, something I've never seen before in my life. WINNER: Matt Hardy. STARS: ***1/2.6. WORLD TAG TEAM TITLES: Lance Cade and Trevor Murdoch vs. Hurricane and Rosey (c)Finally they actually DO something with the tag titles...they'd been on the superheroes since Backlash. Fairly short, but pretty good anyway. Murdoch gives Hurricane a sick DDT on the floor, so he and Cade can wear down Rosey. A groggy Hurricane makes a mistake by tagging himself back in, and is quickly finished off.WINNERS: Cade and Murdoch. STARS: ***.7. Chris Masters vs. Shawn MichaelsSurprisingly good. Michaels carries Masters almost flawlessly in a great contest with some real suspense. In the end, Michaels does not break the Master Lock hold, but he does sidestep it and put Masters' lights out with Sweet Chin Music for the win.WINNER: Shawn Michaels. STARS: ***1/2.8. WWE TITLE: Kurt Angle vs. John Cena (c)These two have always been great together, and tonight is no exception. Cena had been champ too long, and even fans in the arenas were getting tired of him...Angle had an equal amount of support from the fans here, even though he was the bad guy. A very good main event here, except for the ending; Eric Bischoff interfered, and Cena got frustrated and hit Angle with the title belt, getting himself DQed. He then FU'ed Bischoff in the ring, FU'ed Angle through the Spanish announce table, and walked back up the ramp with the title. Disappointing ending or not, this match delivered.WINNER: Kurt Angle by DQ; Cena retains title. STARS: ***1/2.All in all, this PPV was slightly above average. Which is pretty darn good for WWE, these days.(NOTE: Also, it'd be nice if certain immature individuals could stop spamming the WWE product review pages with infantile arguments, obvious bias, and uninformed predictions. If you want to whine about which WWE "brand" is better, go to the PW Forums.Amazon.com is not a forum where you can type anything you please. Get that through your heads already.)
summary: A Very Good PPV (by WWE standards)

reviewText: Unforgiven was a fantastic ppv. This ppv started and continued some good feuds and also had some very great matches. The ppv was very well put together.1. Intercontinental TitleRic Flair vs. CarlitoThis was a great opener. It did everything what an opener is supposed to do, it got the crowd pumped for the ppv. Carlito trys to work on the arm of Flair. It had a nice little brawl on the outside. The crowd really went nuts when Flair pulled off a successful move off the top rope. Also had a good finish to the match. 3.75/52. Divas Tag MatchTrish Stratus & Ashley vs. Victoria & Torrie Wilson w/ Candice MichelleThis tag match really impressed me. It was quite good. Victoria and Torrie isolates Ashley in this one and teaching her what wrestling is all about. Ashley does however gets thrown to the outside very roughly to say the least by Torrie. Trish had a good showing. Trish pulled off a good counter at the end to score with the chick kick. 3.25/53. Big Show vs. Gene SnitzkyUgly match but this too was quite a good match with these two big men. Good impact moves and Snitzky even hits a good looking back suplex on Show. The after match assault with the ring bell added more to the match. 3.5/54. Shelton Benjamin vs. Kerwin White (Chavo Guerrero)A good athletic match up here. They pulled off good counters and reversals. Some nice holds were used too. Shelton pulled off a great counter into the t-bone for the win. 3.5/55. Steel Cage MatchMatt Hardy vs. Edge w/ LitaThis is defiantely one of the most personal feuds ever in the WWE. It went a little slow at first but picked up as the match progressed. Hardy hit Edge with some hard right fists. Hardy takes some hard shots to the back of his head from the steel cage. Edge really then works on the head of Hardy shortly after. Both men hit some high risk moves including a powerbomb & a side effect from the top rope. Edge gets pretty bloody here. Edge also speared Hardy into the cage. The fans was really into this match. Great end with the leg drop off the top of the cage onto edge. 4.5/56. World Tag Team TitlesLance Cade & Trevor Murdoch vs. Hurricane & RoseyAverage tag match. A few double teaming here and there. Hurricane takes a hard ddt on the floor by Murdoch which took Hurricane out. The match pretty much turned into a handicap match after that but still a decent tag match. 3.25/57. Chris Masters vs. Shawn MichaelsFrom the start Masters goes for the masterlock and hbk got in good counters to get out of those situations. They had a good brawl on the outside. Masters even powerbombs hbk into the ring post on the outside. Masters works on the back of hbk. Masters also stays in control for the majority of the match and just punishing hbk's back. I was surprised when Masters used Lex Luger's torture rack on Michaels. Great closing counters at the ending of the match. Great match. Probably Masters best match in the WWE. 4.75/58. WWE ChampionshipKurt Angle vs. John CenaThis is also one of Cena's better matches he has fought in. Angle of course was just phenomenal and just applying submission holds on Cena. Cena also wrestled this match which was great to see. It did became a slugfest between the two at some points in the match. Angle hit cena with some good suplexes. Angle pulled off some good counters and reversals to cena's moves. A lot of close near pin falls. The dq was only to continue the rivaly and the brawl after the match & the FU through the announce table was pretty good. Good way to end the night and to continue the rivaly. 4/5This is one of the best Unforgiven ppvs ever so I recommend on picking this up.

reviewText: On September 18, 2005 w/the success of VENGEANCE 2005 this is another AWESOME RAW PPV from 2005WWE Unforgiven was AWESOME and this was better than all of the other Unforgiven PPV's that I have ever seen.I mean you had 8 Matches, 3 Championship Matches, 2 Tag Team Matches, lot of Grudge Matches, and you even had that Unforgiving Steel Cage Match, plus for the 1st time ever you had the LIVE PPV @ the Ford Center in Jim Ross's Hometown of Oklahoma City, OK, I mean what more could you ask for.and now, here are my thoughts:Ric Flair vs. Carlito for the WWE Intercontinental Championship-This was an AWESOME way to start the show w/Flair winning the I-C Gold for the very 1st time, and becoming the oldest I-C Champion and the oldest Triple Crown Winner in WWE History.DIVA Tag Action Trish & Ashley vs. Victoria & Torrie w/Candice-This was a pretty good match, Victoria looking very sexy and strong and she put a good hurtin' on Ashley, but Trish gets the win for her team w/the Chick Kick, Trish still remains undefeated @ Unforgiven w/a 4-0 record, but what's up w/Torrie bailing on her partner? I don't understand that.Big Show vs. Snitsky-Big Grudge Match-Another great grueling match, but @ the end Big Show wins w/the chokeslam and hitting Snitsky over the head w/the ring bell for payback, WOW!Shelton Banjamin vs. Kerwin White (Chavo Guerrero)-2 former SD! WWE Tag Team Champions, they've faced each other before in Tag Team Matches, but this was 1-on-1, Shelton picks up an easy win w/the T-Bone Suplex, another win for the 3x I-C Champ.Matt Hardy vs. Edge w/Lita-Steel Cage Grudge Match-Of course me being a Cage Match Fanatic, This my friends is what stole the show, I mean Edge & Hardy FINALLY settled their differences in the Cage, w/Hardy giving Lita the Twist of Fate, he also gave Edge the biggest Leg Drop off the Top of the Cage and got the V for Victory, I give this match 5 Stars.Cade & Murdoch vs. Hurricane Helms and Rosey-RAW World Tag Team Titles-a pretty good match, but @ the end the 2 Cowboys picks up the win.HBK Shawn Michaels vs. The Masterpiece Chris Masters-Special Challenge Match-HBK proved that he is INDEED The Showstopper, Masters gave him a great match, but @ the end it was the Sweet Chin Music that got HBK the victory, another BIG win by the 3x WWE Triple Crown Winner HBK.John Cena vs. Kurt Angle-WWE Championship-These 2 put on one heck of a performance, but the ending was kind of premature w/a DQ on Cena, but Bischoff and Angle suffered the FU from Cena, and a good way to end the show.Also Ric Flair partied All Night w/the ladies in his Limousine and Lilian Garcia the woman w/a beautiful singing voice, introduced the legendary ZZ TOP, prior to the Big Show/Snitsky Match.also there were a couple of extras on the DVD, one has Maria Interviewing ZZ Top and it was a short one, and ZZ TOP said to Maria that "Everybody's crazy about a sharped dressed girl". That was so cute when Maria smiled.and another extra one there was the Wild West 8-Man Tag Team from RAW the night after Unforgiven John Cena, Big Show, HBK, and Matt Hardy vs. Kurt Angle, Snitsky, The Masterpiece, and Edge, it was an awesome match, but @ the end it was Big Show dominating the match and hitting the Choke Slam on Edge and everyone did a Gang Pile for the 3-Count, a nice photo finsh.This is an AWESOME DVD and if you didn't see it, then I strongly recommend that you get this DVD, you are going to love it, and the theme to UNFORGIVEN Calling by Taproot is an awesome song, and just so it happens that I have both the Unforgiven DVD and the Taproot CD Blue Sky Research.Vengeance 2005, Unforgiven 2005, and Taboo Tuesday 2005 are truly Must Haves for your DVD collection, they are awesome.

reviewText: Carlito Caribbean Cool VS Ric FlairAn interesting choice to start of the show, but I guess the crowd is so into Flair, that having him come out first wasn't a half bad idea. I loved the Carlito strut. He has a great sense of humour, and ouch what a hard first chop that was. Poor Carlito. The match started at an extremely slow pace, but with Flair in there we probably could have expected it. They worked a very old-school type match. I am a huge fan of working a body part, provided its done well. Carlito working on Flair's arm was done really well. The Hammerlock into the ring post, the hot shot over the rope and various holds, the arm DDT made the working of the arm a joy to watch. Carlito was more aggressive tonight than he usually is, and believe me it's a good thing. It made him look good in the ring. Don't get me wrong, Carlito is totally carrying Flair tonight. I loved the sarcastic ovation when Flair came off the top with the axe handle. I'm still laughing. Nice dropkick into Flair coming off the top. I'm very surprised to see Flair win. Rest assured Carlito will have it back soon. Solid opener tonight.Match Rating: 6.5/10Trish Stratus / Ashley VS Victoria / Torrie WilsonThis was in my opinion the best divas match since the one at Wrestlemania 19.The match was good when Trish and Victoria were in the ring, but still decent when the other two were. Ashley looks to have some natural talent in the ring, and she is quite athletic, but still has a very long way to go. I will give it up to all involved though. The match actually went at a pretty decent pace for the majority of it. Nice high spots with Trish, a great pace and wow, what an effort by all involved. This is my second highest scoring divas match of all time I think.Match Rating: 4.5/10HAHAHAHAHA! The segment with Flair was GOLD! I cant stop laughing.The Raw moving segment was great also. 10/10 for these two promos. LolThe Big Show VS SnitskyAs Big Show comes out, a thought passes. "God I hope this is short".Man Snitsky's back acne is huge. I feel sorry for the people that have to wrestle him. Big chops by the Big Show which have become his signature as of late. The crowd is into it, which is surprising. Why take a break from the match to show what happened 3 weeks ago? It looks like the arm is the body part of the night to work on. Great strength by Snitsky to get Show up for a suplex. Say what you will about Snitsky, but he is really carrying Big Show. This match is actually quite good. (I am not kidding). It was never going to be a classic, but with who they have in there it has turned out quite well. You know that your locked into a kicking show when this match comes of alright. As good a pace as you will see for a Big Show match. I'm glad this match was kept short, because if it went any longer it would have sucked. 3 decent matches out of 3 so far. Lets hope the wwe keeps this up.Match Rating: 5.5/10Shelton Benjamin VS Kerwin WhiteI am so glad that this match was put on the card, because both of these guys can go in the ring. A quick jump start to the match is exactly what the doctor ordered in this case. Huge Flapjack by Benjamin, and after some quick momentum, Kerwin gets working on Shelton's leg. Awesome flying head-scissor by Kerwin. This match is going at a blistering pace. Benjamin sold the leg injury very well, while still moving quickly in the ring. Nice superplex of the top, and this match is really putting together some great wrestling. Great move for move wrestling. A nice finish, to an absolutely terrific match. With a few more minutes this one could have been even better.Match Rating: 7/10Well that's half the card gone, and so far it has completely beaten Summerslam in terms of match quality.Steel Cage Match: Edge VS Matt HardyThis match has the potential to turn into a spot fest, and I really hope that doesn't happen. A lot of psychology is needed in this one. I'm not a big fan of cage matches, as I generally think that they are overdone and have become rather boring. That's not to say that on any given night there could be a fantastic cage match. The attempted Twist of Fate, push off into the cage and Flashback (that's what I call it) was a nice sequence, and the missile dropkick into the head was good. Edge begins working on the head which is what I want, instead of these two just doing 2 or 3 good spots and calling it a night. I do want to see a high spot or two, but there is more to having a good match than that. Both men are really working in there, and despite their real life issues, it looks like they are really committed to having a solid match. Edge is getting some great heat tonight. Edge executed three powerbombs flawlessly (against the cage, against the turnbuckle and off the top) now this match is really starting to heat up and the crowd is into it. Nice use of the MITB briefcase, and this match has me going! Its about time someone bled haha. Great side effect of the top rope while Lita gets in the ring! DAMMIT! This is exactly what we didn't need in this match. Why just not let them finish the match one on one. Great fake finish with the spear, and by this point the crowd is in a frenzy. BANG! A leg drop of the top and its over! What a fantastic bout. I am not a fan of either Matt Hardy or Edge, or of the gimmick but these two put everything into it and gave us a match to remember. A Match of the Year candidate for sure. For a match I thought would bomb, wow was I proved wrong. Awesome effort by both men. I think this match will get a low mark from some people, but that will be because there weren't endless dives of the cage and such. Ill say it again, there is more to having a good match than just having a huge spot and calling it a night.Match Rating: 9.75/10Hurricane / Rosey VS Lance Cade / Trevor MurdochWow do these two have a tough act to follow, especially in their pay per view debut.Cade and Murdoch have looked a lot better in the last 2 weeks than they did in their debut. They are quite a solid team. Murdoch's facial expressions have me going. When Hurricane is in the ring with whoever they look good, but when rosey is in there its another story. What a great spot, the DDT of the apron onto the floor was brutal. One of the best spots I have seen this year. Well with Hurricane not getting up, we know who is going to win don't we? The match was good and despite Rosey being in the ring for the majority of the time Cade and Murdoch managed to keep the pace of the match going at a reasonably good rate. Hurricane got a cheer when he was being taken out but I think its just a work. The referee didn't throw up the famous "X". Well he is coming back now so yeah. The big question following this match is who are Cade and Murdoch going to feud with now? Have to wait and see tonight.Match Rating: 5/106 average or better matches out of 6. Way to go wwe.Chris Masters VS Shawn MichaelsWell its time for the ppv debut of Masters. If Chris cannot have a good match with Michaels, then there is no hope for him. I hope he has a good match, but this has the potential to be really bad, or surprisingly good for that matter. Lets get into the action.A good way to start the match as it establishes Masters is there to really show us something.. This match reminds me of the Batista VS HBK match at Armageddon 2003 (Batista's best match ever in wwe), where Batista was consistently using his size and power while HBK was countering with speed. It provided a really good contrast between the two competitors. Nice double powerbomb into the post. What is it with working body parts tonight? Just about every match has had working. (Don't get me wrong that's a good thing). Masters is looking impressive tonight. He has already done more moves in this match than in the previous month put together. A powerbomb, delayed suplex, back breaker, torture rack, Gorilla Press and so on.HBK is putting his whole body into every little thing that Masters is doing. Great way to make Masters look good. Masters also looks a lot more mobile than he has in previous months. Wow, I cant get over how good Masters is doing in the ring. Sure being in there with HBK is a great advantage for him, but as I am writing this, this is already the best match in Masters' career. The low blow by HBK really put Masters over. Let me explain. By doing that he told us that Masters was really owning him and he needed to resort to something desperate. Good booking there. The wwe really needs to continue to put Masters in feuds and not just stupid "Masterlock Challenges".An innovative way to get out of the masterlock without actually "breaking" it.A phenominal match, and while I would like to say HBK carried Masters (and he did a little) but Masters was with him every step of the way. Masters stepped up tonight, and has justified his push thus far. Great match.Match Rating: 8/10Kurt Angle VS John CenaAgain a mixed reaction for Cena. Out of all the faces tonight, Cena is the only one that the crowd were not firmly behind. Wonder why? Could be to do with Angle being quite over also. Who knows.Both men came out like a house on fire, until Angle took a spell on the outside. German suplex followed by a "lets go Angle" chant. Can you see the smile on my face Pyro? Haha. Good to see Angle use the belly to belly again. Haven't seen him use that for a while. Somewhat surprising that since Cena has a "hurt" ankle, Angle hasn't gone to work on it yet, instead focusing on the back. Hopefully that is rectified later on in the match. Angle is giving Cena a number of suplexes. He just gave him another German during the replay. Angle and Cena have good chemistry in the ring. They have had it for all 5 or 6 one on one matches they have had together. Tonight is no different. Move for move wrestling by both men is working well, so why change it.The ankle lock into the spinebuster was done well. The crowd is really into it now, and they are still divided. The ref bump was unnecessary I think, as Angle and Cena were tearing the house down before it happened, but when it did, it slowed the match a little. Didn't Cena hit Angle with the medals one time years ago? God why did Bischoff have to come down. Bad booking, just unnecessary. Well Angle wins and the feud will continue I guess. A solid match, up until all the interference.The match rating would have been higher with a clean finish, and no interference. If they just let these two men wrestle a little longer without interference, this match could have been even more awesome.Angle's neck took a little wrong fall on that table. I'm a little worried.Match Rating: 7.5/10Why did the ref raise Cena's hand? He lost! StupidOut of all the pay per views this year, I was expecting this one to be in the bottom 2 or 3. Boy was I wrong. What an amazing show. With the lack of star power (Triple H and that), this ppv was able to put on a great wrestling experience. It was far better than Summerslam last month. It was better than Backlash, and right on par with Vengeance as far as raw ppvs go this year.
